Shin.

282
00:16:36,681 --> 00:16:37,830
Tonight,

283
00:16:38,612 --> 00:16:40,757
I won't be making any eye contact with you.

284
00:16:43,356 --> 00:16:44,437
Why not?

285
00:16:45,921 --> 00:16:47,281
For Minato Akira

286
00:16:49,411 --> 00:16:51,380
to still be Minato Akira.

287
00:17:06,508 --> 00:17:08,845
Thank you for falling asleep.

288
00:17:42,481 --> 00:17:43,717
Can't you sleep?

289
00:17:44,297 --> 00:17:46,632
What? Are you still awake?

290
00:17:48,201 --> 00:17:49,202
A moment ago,

291
00:17:49,290 --> 00:17:50,759
you were looking at me.

292
00:17:53,220 --> 00:17:54,928
You said you wouldn't make eye contact with me.

293
00:17:55,207 --> 00:17:56,288
I didn't.

294
00:17:56,780 --> 00:17:59,514
You closed your eyes. Our eyes didn't meet.

295
00:18:04,896 --> 00:18:06,272
I can't sleep either.

296
00:18:08,554 --> 00:18:10,590
Knowing you were by my side.

297
00:18:15,140 --> 00:18:16,186
Can I...

298
00:18:17,160 --> 00:18:18,498
hold your hands?

299
00:18:22,439 --> 00:18:23,975
We don't need to make eye contact.

300
00:18:25,271 --> 00:18:27,022
Just holding hands is enough.

301
00:18:29,141 --> 00:18:30,309
That way,

302
00:18:32,231 --> 00:18:33,608
I think I can sleep.

303
00:18:38,625 --> 00:18:40,026
All right, I get it.

304
00:18:42,755 --> 00:18:44,090
Just holding hands. That's all.

305
00:19:01,891 --> 00:19:03,241
Your hand...

306
00:19:05,111 --> 00:19:06,170
is so warm.

307
00:19:09,910 --> 00:19:11,684
For a warm-hearted person,

308
00:19:12,512 --> 00:19:14,006
their hands are usually warm.

309
00:19:20,456 --> 00:19:21,727
Are you all right now?

310
00:19:24,884 --> 00:19:25,889
What do you mean?

311
00:19:27,426 --> 00:19:29,061
I mean, Sakuma-sensei.

312
00:19:37,155 --> 00:19:39,157
It's good to have you here.

313
00:19:42,189 --> 00:19:43,716
But it's so embarrassing

314
00:19:44,874 --> 00:19:48,528
for an old man like me
to cry in front of a highschooler.

315
00:19:52,058 --> 00:19:54,026
I don't think it's anything embarrassing.

316
00:19:56,958 --> 00:19:58,538
I find you being like this

317
00:19:59,445 --> 00:20:00,933
is kind of cute.

318
00:20:03,235 --> 00:20:04,272
But...

319
00:20:07,506 --> 00:20:09,467
I can't help wonder.
I like you so much.

320
00:20:11,343 --> 00:20:12,945
But why can't I be the person

321
00:20:14,413 --> 00:20:15,781
that you like?

322
00:20:22,019 --> 00:20:23,108
Anyway,

323
00:20:25,185 --> 00:20:26,586
holding your hand like this...

324
00:20:29,485 --> 00:20:30,889
already makes me happy.

325
00:20:35,876 --> 00:20:37,444
Just this little instance...

326
00:20:39,311 --> 00:20:41,311
could make me so happy.

327
00:20:48,459 --> 00:20:49,522
Minato-san.

328
00:20:51,467 --> 00:20:52,918
Thank you very much

329
00:20:54,051 --> 00:20:55,354
for coming here with me.

330
00:20:58,791 --> 00:21:00,006
Good night.

331
00:21:03,368 --> 00:21:04,467
Yeah.

332
00:21:05,895 --> 00:21:06,990
Good night.

333
00:21:15,424 --> 00:21:16,909
Shin's feelings,

334
00:21:19,734 --> 00:21:20,980
his thoughts

335
00:21:24,029 --> 00:21:25,494
have passed through his hand.

336
00:21:25,797 --> 00:21:27,640
I can feel it that it hurts.

337
00:21:43,919 --> 00:21:45,849
We're back.

338
00:21:49,457 --> 00:21:50,935
Tokyo was nice.

339
00:21:51,430 --> 00:21:53,491
But I like our hometown better.

340
00:21:55,685 --> 00:21:56,794
Akira-san.

341
00:21:58,965 --> 00:22:01,871
Thank you for taking me along with you.

342
00:22:02,717 --> 00:22:04,200
What's with you, Asuka?

343
00:22:04,842 --> 00:22:06,664
It's your first time thanking me.

344
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:09,060
You, too, Shin.

345
00:22:09,433 --> 00:22:10,560
Thank you.

346
00:22:11,964 --> 00:22:13,130
What did I do?

347
00:22:14,300 --> 00:22:15,955
All right. My house is that way.

348
00:22:19,366 --> 00:22:20,911
Even though I don't quite understand it.

349
00:22:21,391 --> 00:22:23,209
But I guess he's grown up.

350
00:22:25,752 --> 00:22:26,771
Shin.

351
00:22:27,040 --> 00:22:28,232
Wanna come to the laundromat?

352
00:22:28,726 --> 00:22:29,779
Yes.

353
00:22:30,003 --> 00:22:31,044
Let's go.

354
00:22:39,098 --> 00:22:40,130
Shuu-kun.

355
00:22:41,845 --> 00:22:42,880
Asuka.

356
00:22:43,747 --> 00:22:44,930
You're back.

357
00:22:51,968 --> 00:22:53,021
I...

358
00:22:56,370 --> 00:22:58,172
I like you, Shuu-kun.

359
00:23:07,253 --> 00:23:08,450
I'm back.

360
00:23:10,547 --> 00:23:11,824
Want one, too?

361
00:23:14,018 --> 00:23:15,028
Here.

362
00:23:17,449 --> 00:23:18,560
Minato-san.

363
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:22,521
From now on,

364
00:23:23,254 --> 00:23:24,857
I'll stop seeing you.

365
00:23:30,678 --> 00:23:31,682
(Minato Shouji Coin Laundry)

366
00:23:31,707 --> 00:23:33,489
Even when the weather forecast
made a mistake,

367
00:23:34,203 --> 00:23:36,715
Minato's Laundromat
is still open for business as usual.

368
00:23:36,739 --> 00:23:37,728
(Minato Shouji Coin Laundry)

369
00:23:37,728 --> 00:23:40,352
Please continue to support us next week.

370
